node.contents: Yes, Hotspot JVM already knows about the intrinsics, but they should be declared in the class library. So you'll need to either patch `rt.jar` (replace Unsafe.class) or prepend the [modified Unsafe.class](https://docs.google.com/file/d/0B7LUxTf0AV-faDBWRzE3UzVFa2M) to boot classpath using `-Xbootclasspath/p` flag.

node.contents: Can you comment on `-XX:AllocatePrefetchLines` JVM option? Does it enable prefetch?

astNode.text: Can you comment on `-XX:AllocatePrefetchLines` JVM option? Does it enable prefetch?

node.contents: @neverov All `AllocatePrefetch*` options are related to emitting `prefetch` instructions right after object allocation in Java Heap. This is controlled by `-XX:AllocatePrefetchStyle` option which is ON by default. `AllocatePrefetchLines` and `AllocateInstancePrefetchLines` control how far (in number of cache lines) to prefetch after the address of allocated object, for an array or an object respectively.

node.contents:
One interesting thing is that Hotspot JVM actually does support prefetch!
It treats Unsafe.prefetchRead() and Unsafe.prefetchWrite() methods as intrinsics and compiles them into corresponding CPU instructions.

astNode.text:
One interesting thing is that Hotspot JVM actually does support prefetch!
It treats Unsafe.prefetchRead() and Unsafe.prefetchWrite() methods as intrinsics and compiles them into corresponding CPU instructions.

node.contents: Unfortunately, sun.misc.Unsafe does not declare such methods. But, if you add the following methods to Unsafe.java, recompile it and replace Unsafe.class inside rt.jar (or just add -Xbootclasspath/p JVM argument) you would be able to use prefetch intrinsics in your application.

astNode.text: Unfortunately, sun.misc.Unsafe does not declare such methods. But, if you add the following methods to Unsafe.java, recompile it and replace Unsafe.class inside rt.jar (or just add -Xbootclasspath/p JVM argument) you would be able to use prefetch intrinsics in your application.

elements.contents: public native void prefetchRead(Object o, long offset); public native void prefetchWrite(Object o, long offset); public static native void prefetchReadStatic(Object o, long offset); public static native void prefetchWriteStatic(Object o, long offset);
